    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nWe currently allow `except +nogil` and parse it as `except + nogil` (with space). However, that is different from `except +handlerfunc`. We should require it to be spelled `except + nogil`.\r\n\r\nWe should also consider rejecting `except +nogil` all together and not parse it as exception handler function. It's an easy source of typos.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\r\ncdef func() except +nogil:\r\n    pass\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n_No response_\n\n### OS\n\n_No response_\n\n### Python version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Cython version\n\n0.29.x and master\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "It's quite unfortunate that the ordering of except vs. nogil now makes the white-space after `except +` semantically relevant. If only to mitigate that, I fully agree that `+nogil` should be forbidden.\r\n\r\nI tried chasing down the decision for the ordering, and AFAICT, it was [made](https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4670#discussion_r854489596) directly in the PR. So, for completeness, a comparison of all possible combinations:\r\n\r\n### Current status: first `except` qualifier, then `gil` qualifier\r\n```\r\nnoexcept nogil:\r\nnoexcept with gil:\r\nexcept <val> nogil:\r\nexcept <val> with gil:\r\nexcept? <val> nogil:\r\nexcept? <val> with gil:\r\nexcept * nogil:\r\nexcept * with gil:\r\nexcept + nogil:                # only separated from `except +<handler>` (without gil-qualifier) by a single space\r\nexcept + with gil:\r\nexcept +* nogil:\r\nexcept +* with gil:\r\nexcept +<PyError> nogil:\r\nexcept +<PyError> with gil:\r\nexcept +<handler> nogil:\r\nexcept +<handler> with gil:\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere are IMO a bunch more cases above where presumably the space before `nogil` / `with gil` should be made mandatory, even though we might parse correctly without it (like `except *nogil`).\r\n\r\n### Parallel world: first `gil` qualifier, then `except` qualifier\r\n\r\n```\r\nnogil noexcept:\r\nnogil except <val>:\r\nnogil except? <val>:\r\nnogil except *:\r\nnogil except +:\r\nnogil except +*:\r\nnogil except +<PyError>:\r\nnogil except +<handler>:\r\nwith gil noexcept:\r\nwith gil except <val>:\r\nwith gil except? <val>:\r\nwith gil except *:\r\nwith gil except +:\r\nwith gil except +*:\r\nwith gil except +<PyError>:\r\nwith gil except +<handler>:\r\n```\r\n\r\nPersonally I think the second set looks better, aside from the fact that it does not suffer from any ambiguity or semantically relevant whitespace. But I also guess it's too late to change it now that we're in the beta phase already and projects have started responding to the warnings about the ordering.",
